00:01:01.570 --> 00:01:04.000
the top 1% of web designers.

00:01:04.239 --> 00:01:09.220
So question number one is, how do I
pick the right fonts for my project?

00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:12.235
Most web designers use
the same free fonts.

00:01:12.820 --> 00:01:14.200
Over and over again.

00:01:14.290 --> 00:01:18.280
And when you use those same fonts as
everyone else, your designs start to

00:01:18.280 --> 00:01:23.410
blend in, not stand out, so you gotta find
fonts from places that aren't overused.

00:01:23.440 --> 00:01:30.130
Two of my favorite resources are
font share.com and uncut.wtf.

00:01:30.970 --> 00:01:35.710
Font share is clean, high
quality, and completely free to

00:01:35.710 --> 00:01:37.975
use while uncut is a bit more.

00:01:38.370 --> 00:01:44.160
Experimental, but they're both packed with
personality and tons of free fonts to use.

00:01:44.190 --> 00:01:48.060
Oh, and I've got a running list
of free and affordable fonts

00:01:48.060 --> 00:01:50.100
that I found out in the wild.

00:01:50.130 --> 00:01:52.680
Every one of them are Chefs Kiss.

00:01:52.710 --> 00:01:57.390
So you're gonna find the link to that
list in the description of this video.

00:01:57.420 --> 00:01:59.095
Oh, and by the way,
make sure that you like.

00:01:59.395 --> 00:02:02.095
And subscribe so you don't
